
[1]beatitude

   BEAT'ITUDE, n. [L. beatitudo, from beatus, beo. See Beatify.]

   1. Blessedness; felicity of the highest kind; consummate bliss; used of
   the joys of heaven.

   2. The declaration of blessedness made by our Savior to particular
   virtues.
